body:
Hi folks,



I have downloaded the radiation in urban canyon example and I am getting some strange results and behaviour.



Firstly all my radiation results are zero secondly this appears to be due to the fact that there is a KeyError(1,) going on.



Mostapha any idea whats going on? If so can I fix it ; )
topic: Radiation in an urban Canyon selectedSkyMtx component

replies.body: Sorry I forgot to attach the file.

Hi Anton,

Attached a working file.

When i opened your it kind of went into an endless loop. CAn't say exactly why.

At the end i updated the file and it is working fine now.

-A.

Hi Abraham

Thanks however I am still getting the key error issue.

I would suspect of the gendaymtx.exe. Can be?

Also try closing GH and Rhino, and start from fresh. It worked for me yesterday with the file i fixed.

Otherwise ... can't tell, since the file i uploaded works for me.

-A.

It's almost always the issue with gendaymtx being blocked.

Anton, did you unblock gendaymtx.exe? You also need to set useOldRes to False. There are several discussions on this topic if you search the discussions.
